## Complete Example

```lua
loadstring(game:HttpGet("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/10cxm/millenium-fixed/main/scr"))()

library:update_theme("accent", Color3.fromRGB(255, 100, 150))

local window = library:window({
    name = "MyScript",
    suffix = "V1",
    gameInfo = "Game Name",
    size = UDim2.new(0, 700, 0, 565)
})

local main, settings = window:tab({
    name = "Main",
    icon = "rbxassetid://6034767608",
    tabs = {"Combat", "Settings"}
})

local column = main:column({size = 1})
local section = column:section({
    name = "Features",
    size = 1,
    icon = "rbxassetid://6022668898"
})

section:toggle({
    name = "Enable Aimbot",
    default = false,
    callback = function(val)
        print("Aimbot:", val)
    end
})

section:slider({
    name = "FOV",
    min = 50,
    max = 500,
    default = 150,
    callback = function(val)
        print("FOV:", val)
    end
})

section:dropdown({
    name = "Target",
    items = {"Head", "Torso", "Random"},
    default = "Head",
    callback = function(val)
        print("Target:", val)
    end
})

section:colorpicker({
    name = "Color",
    color = Color3.fromRGB(255, 0, 0),
    callback = function(color, alpha)
        print("Color:", color)
    end
})

library.notifications:create_notification({
    name = "Script Loaded",
    info = "All features ready!",
    lifetime = 3
})

window.toggle_menu(true)
```

---

## Flag System

Flags store element values for configs:

```lua
library.flags["element_flag"]
library.config_flags["element_flag"]
```

Access toggle state:
```lua
if library.flags["my_toggle"] then
    print("Toggle is enabled")
end
```

Access slider value:
```lua
local fov = library.flags["fov_slider"]
```

Access color:
```lua
local color = library.flags["my_color"]
local colorValue = color.Color
local transparency = color.Transparency
```

---

## Tips

1. **Flags**: Always set unique flag names for config saving
2. **Callbacks**: Use callbacks for real-time updates
3. **Sections**: Use `fading = true` to make collapsible sections
4. **Multi-select**: Set `multi = true` on dropdowns for multiple selections
5. **Info Text**: Use `info` parameter to add helpful descriptions
6. **Separators**: Use `seperator = true` to add visual separation
7. **Theme**: Set accent color before creating window
8. **Notifications**: Use for user feedback and status updates

---

## Common Patterns

### Toggle with Keybind
```lua
local toggle = section:toggle({
    name = "Feature",
    callback = function(val) end
})

section:keybind({
    name = "Toggle Key",
    callback = function(val)
        toggle.set(val)
    end
})
```

### Slider with Visual Feedback
```lua
section:slider({
    name = "Value",
    min = 0,
    max = 100,
    callback = function(val)
        library.notifications:create_notification({
            name = "Updated",
            info = "Value: " .. val
        })
    end
})
```

### Colorpicker with Theme Update
```lua
section:colorpicker({
    name = "UI Color",
    color = Color3.fromRGB(155, 150, 219),
    callback = function(color, alpha)
        library:update_theme("accent", color)
    end
})
```

### Dropdown with Dynamic Options
```lua
local dropdown = section:dropdown({
    name = "Players",
    items = {}
})

game.Players.PlayerAdded:Connect(function()
    local players = {}
    for _, player in game.Players:GetPlayers() do
        table.insert(players, player.Name)
    end
    dropdown.refresh_options(players)
end)
```
